//----------------------------Policies-----------------------------//
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Policy?

üëâ A Policy is a class that contains permission rules
Can user edit this post?
Can user delete this post?
Policy = centralized permission rules
2Ô∏è‚É£ Create a Policy
php artisan make:policy PostPolicy --model=Post

generate the PostPolicy.php in app/Policies

3Ô∏è‚É£-Add your rule
public function update(User $user, Post $post): bool
{
    return $user->id === $post->user_id;
}

public function delete(User $user, Post $post): bool
{
    return $user->id === $post->user_id;
}

Allow only if:
user.id == post.user_id

4Ô∏è‚É£ Register the Policy for old version by adding code below to app/Providers/AuthServiceProvider.php
use App\Models\Post;
use App\Policies\PostPolicy;

protected $policies = [
    Post::class => PostPolicy::class,
];

5Ô∏è‚É£ Use Policy in Controller in update,edit and delete function
$this->authorize('update', $post); ==>edit and update
$this->authorize('delete', $post); ==> delete
**ERROR might show for editeing which solce by adding below to controller

use Illuminate\Foundation\Auth\Access\AuthorizesRequests;
use Illuminate\Foundation\Validation\ValidatesRequests;
use Illuminate\Routing\Controller as BaseController;

abstract class Controller extends BaseController
{
    use AuthorizesRequests, ValidatesRequests;
}

